# Dynamic CDR Decoder

## Objective
Develop a dynamic decoder for ASN.1 encoded IMS VoLTE CDR files.

## Files
- ims.asn1 (ASN.1 schema)
- Sample DAT file
- Python decoder code

## Tech Stack
- Python
-Django,MySQL
- ASN.1
- pyasn1 / asn1tools
- JSON

CDR Decoder — Progress Update
Done:
Built BER/ASN.1 decoder (cdr_decoder.py) — decodes .dat CDR files using ims.asn1 schema into JSON
Tested on NZDLVOLTE202603201155167848.dat — all 10 records decode correctly (caller/called no., duration, timestamps, IMSI, IMEI, codecs, etc.)
Set up Django project (cdr_project, cdr_app, decoder folders) with DRF + MySQL client
Created models: IMSVoiceRecord (78 fields) and CDRRule (dynamic rules — field, operator, value, action stored in DB, no hardcoding)
Wrote backend logic: views.py (upload → decode → save → apply rules), rule_engine.py (reads rules from DB dynamically), serializers.py, urls.py
API endpoints ready: /api/upload/, /api/records/, /api/rules/
Built basic HTML/JS dashboard — upload file, view records table, add/delete rules

